\section{Naming convention}{

The \code{met_} prefix on all six within-environment design functions
(\code{met_prep_famoptg()}, \code{met_alpha_rc_stream()},
\code{met_evaluate_famoptg_efficiency()}, \code{met_evaluate_alpha_efficiency()},
\code{met_optimize_famoptg()}, \code{met_optimize_alpha_rc()}) distinguishes
them from their counterparts in the OptiDesign package. Both packages can
be loaded simultaneously without namespace conflicts.
}

\section{Example data}{

\code{OptiSparseMET_example_data} is a synthetic dataset containing treatment
vectors, environment names, family metadata, seed inventories, relationship
matrices (GRM, A, K), and pre-built argument lists for allocation and local
design functions. All components refer to the same set of synthetic lines
and environments and can be passed to any package function without
modification. Load with:

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode r">}}\preformatted{data("OptiSparseMET_example_data", package = "OptiSparseMET")
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}

\section{Dependencies}{

\strong{Matrix} is used for sparse matrix operations in efficiency evaluation and
design construction. \strong{pracma} provides \code{mod()} for serpentine traversal
logic in \code{met_alpha_rc_stream()} and \code{met_prep_famoptg()}.
}

